def data_cleaning(row):
    # 2. replace null values with average values in the level 1 and level 2 columns
    
    df['Level 1'].fillna(value = round(df['Level 1'].mean(),2), inplace = True)
    df['Level 2'].fillna(value = round(df['Level 2'].mean(),2), inplace = True)
    
    # 3.In column ‘B’ replace Jan with january, feb with february, march with march, 
    
    df.replace({'Month': {'Jan': 'January','Feb': 'February', 'Mar': 'March', 'Apr': 'April','Jun': 'June',
    'Jul': 'July','Aug': 'August', 'Sep': 'September','Oct': 'October','Nov': 'November', 'Dec': 'December'}}, inplace = True)
    
    # 4.In column ‘E’ Replace “Came_From_LinkedIn” with “From LinkedIn” and “Landed_Directly” with “Direct_traffic”
    
    df['Coming from'] = df['Coming from'].apply(lambda x: x.replace('Landed_Directly', 'Direct_traffic'))
    df['Coming from'] = df['Coming from'].apply(lambda x: x.replace('Came_From_LinkedIn', 'From LinkedIn'))
    
    # 1. 1.Create a column at the end, named “inc/dec percentage”, (“Level 1” – “Level 4”) / “Level 1” * 100
    # which would give the growth/reduction percentage in numbers of level 1 vs level 4 columns   
    
    df['inc/dec percentage'] = round(((df['Level 1'] - df['Level 4'])/(df['Level 1']))*100, 2)

def descriptive_stats(Year, Month, Laptop_Desktop, Type_of_Customers, Coming_from):
    
    # Minimum of Level1, Level2, Level3, Level4
    min_val = df[['Level 1','Level 2','Level 3','Level 4']].min()
    
    # Give the maximum value of “Level 2” / “Level 1” among those who came directly to the via desktop website
    df['Level2/Level1'] = df['Level 2']/df['Level 1']
    max_ratio = df.loc[(df['Laptop/Desktop'] == 'Desktop_Website')]
    max_value = max_ratio['Level2/Level1'].max()
    
    # let the new dataframe be newdf
    newdf = df.loc[(df['Year'] == Year) & (df['Month'] == Month) & (df['Laptop/Desktop'] == Laptop_Desktop) & (df['Type_of_Customers?'] == Type_of_Customers) & (df['Coming from'] ==Coming_from)]
    
    # Generates the summary statistics
    des_stat = newdf.describe()
    
    return (print('The new Dataframe \n'),
            display(newdf),
            print('The descriptive stats of the new dataframe \n'),
            display(des_stat),
            print('minimum value in the columns\n',min_val, '\n'),
            print('the max value of ratio level2/level1 for Desktop_Website is: ', max_value, '\n'),
            print('The Unique value in Month column is\n', newdf['Month'].unique(),'\n','The data type is\n', newdf['Month'].dtype, '\n'),
           print('The Unique value in Laptop/Desktop column is\n', newdf['Laptop/Desktop'].unique(),'\n','The data type is\n', newdf['Laptop/Desktop'].dtype, '\n'),
           print('The Unique value in Type_of_Customers? column is\n', newdf['Type_of_Customers?'].unique(),'\n','The data type is\n', newdf['Type_of_Customers?'].dtype, '\n'),
            print('The Unique value in Coming from column is\n', newdf['Coming from'].unique(),'\n','The data type is\n', newdf['Coming from'].dtype, '\n'),
           )

# creating the sum of level 4 column
df['sum_of_level4'] = df['Level 4'].sum()

# Adding rank according to level 4 columnd
df['rank'] = df.groupby('Year')['Level 4'].rank(ascending=False)
df = df.sort_values(by = 'rank')

In [61]:
#Ho: It is non stationary
#H1: It is stationary

def adfuller_test(sales):
    result=adfuller(sales)
    labels = ['ADF Test Statistic','p-value','#Lags Used','Number of Observations Used']
    for value,label in zip(result,labels):
        print(label+' : '+str(value) )
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("strong evidence against the null hypothesis(Ho), reject the null hypothesis. Data has no unit root and is stationary")
    else:
        print("weak evidence against null hypothesis, time series has a unit root, indicating it is non-stationary ")

Part 6: About the Previous projects¶

● Please describe any interesting project you did in the Data Science domain in more than 250 words. Attach Github links if possible.

During my internship at Innomatics Research Labs one of the projects that excited me was application development on streamlit of Diamond Price prediction machine learning model. This project objective was to predict the price of the Diamond given the input parameter like cut, depth, height etc. And to develop a web based application using Streamlit. The classic Diamonds dataset contains the prices and other attributes of almost 54,000 diamonds. The dataset contains 53940 rows and 10 variables. The methodology of the project is as follow

  1. Perform the Exploratory data analysis. The EDA mainly focused on the cleaning the dataset, checking for null values, outlier detection and applying visualization tools to understand the relationships and distributions of the data.
  2. Under visualization the box plot was used to detect the outliers present in the data. The pair plot was used to visualize the relationship and trend that was hidden in the data. The Heat map was used to study the correlation between the independent variable and dependent variable to understand the impact of each independent variable on the dependent variable.
  3. Feature engineering: The categorical variables were encoded before the model development.
  4. Model Development: Few different Regression models were implemented to study the performances and to select the optimum performing model.
  5. Pickling: The optimum performing model was converted into pickle file using the Serialization technique for the application development.
  6. Application Development – Streamlit: The trained pickled model was un-pickled and used in the application development. The input data from user was converted into suitable form in order to perform the prediction.
  7. Github link = https://github.com/rohith7799/Diamond-Price-Prediction-Streamlit-App

Part 7: Time management¶

● Can you please share your thoughts, in less than 120 words, on “If you get selected, how will you manage your time for this full-time internship opportunity”

  1. Prioritize tasks by importance and urgency.
  2. Devote the considerable amount of time on the task that is in hand.
  3. Communicating with fellow interns/colleagues for help.
  4. Try to learn new concepts regarding the task with the help of mentors and friends.
  5. Ask Mentors/Manager for help whenever there is a need of it.
  6. Start day early with clear goal and target that needs to be done.
  7. Talking to Mentors/Manager in the beginning to get their feedback on priorities and how long they feel tasks should take.
